  96:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****     This subsection provides a set of functions allowing to control the RCC Clocks
  97:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****     frequencies.
  98:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****     [..]
  99:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****     (@) Important note: Care must be taken when HAL_RCCEx_PeriphCLKConfig() is used to
 100:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****         select the RTC clock source; in this case the Backup domain will be reset in
 101:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****         order to modify the RTC Clock source, as consequence RTC registers (including
 102:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****         the backup registers) and RCC_BDCR register are set to their reset values.
